    • Method Detail

      • numericRowWriter

        public static NumericRowWriter numericRowWriter​(java.util.List<java.lang.String> columnLabels,
                                                java.util.List<ColumnType<java.lang.Void>> types,
                                                boolean initialize)
        Writer for a new Table consisting of numeric columns with the given column labels and types and an unknown number of rows. If the number of rows can be estimated, use numericRowWriter(List, List, int, boolean) instead to prevent unnecessary resizing of the data containers. If unset values should be missing, choose true for initialize, if there are no unset values choose false for performance reasons.
        Parameters:
        columnLabels - the labels of the columns
        types - the types of the columns, either ColumnTypes.INTEGER or ColumnTypes.REAL
        initialize - if this is true every value that is not explicitly set is missing, if this is false values for indices that are not explicitly set are undetermined
        Returns:
        a writer to write a new table row by row
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if column label or type list is null or contains null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if column label list is empty or not the same size as types list or the types contain a type that is neither ColumnTypes.INTEGER nor ColumnTypes.REAL

        public static NumericRowWriter realRowWriter​(java.util.List<java.lang.String> columnLabels,
                                             int expectedRows,
                                             boolean initialize)
        Writer for a new Table consisting of real columns with the given column labels and the given expected number of rows. If unset values should be missing, choose true for initialize, if there are no unset values choose false for performance reasons.
        Parameters:
        columnLabels - the labels of the columns
        expectedRows - an estimate for the number of rows in the final table. A good estimation prevents unnecessary resizing of the data containers.
        initialize - if this is true every value that is not explicitly set is missing, if this is false values for indices that are not explicitly set are undetermined
        Returns:
        a writer to write a new table row by row
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if columnLabels is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if column label list is empty or expected rows are negative

      • mixedRowWriter

        public static MixedRowWriter mixedRowWriter​(java.util.List<java.lang.String> columnLabels,
                                            java.util.List<ColumnType<?>> types,
                                            boolean initialize)
        Writer for a new Table consisting of non-numeric columns with the given column labels and types and an unknown number of rows. If the number of rows can be estimated, use mixedRowWriter(List, List, int, boolean) instead to prevent unnecessary resizing of the data containers. If all types are numeric use numericRowWriter(List, List, boolean) instead. If unset values should be missing, choose true for initialize, if there are no unset values choose false for performance reasons.
        Parameters:
        columnLabels - the labels of the columns
        types - the types of the columns
        initialize - if this is true every value that is not explicitly set is missing, if this is false values for indices that are not explicitly set are undetermined
        Returns:
        a writer to write a new table row by row
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if column label or type list is null or contains null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if column label list is empty or not the same size as types list
